sec.p:
The reliability of the finite element model was evaluated through quantitative comparison with experimental data for peak temperature, heat-affected zone width, stir zone hardness, and ultimate tensile strength under identical processing conditions. As summarized in Table 4, the model demonstrated strong predictive accuracy, with all deviations below 5%. Coefficients of determination (
R 2
) exceed 0.985 and p-values are below 0.001 for all parameters, confirming that the simulations capture experimental variability across the full parameter space.
